## Activity Type Patterns

Look at the page image to determine the activity type, then use the appropriate HTML pattern:

### Multiple Choice (radio buttons)
Use when: Students pick ONE correct answer from several options per question.
- Input: `<input type="radio" name="question-group-N" value="item-N" data-activity-item="item-N" class="sr-only" tabindex="0" />`
- Option markers: Sequential numbers (1, 2, 3...) in `.option-letter`, NOT letters
- Each option needs `data-activity-item="item-N"` and `data-id` on the text element

### True/False (radio buttons)
Use when: Students label statements as "true" or "false".
- Structure: `<fieldset>` with `<legend>` containing the question
- Two radio buttons per question sharing the same `data-activity-item` value
- Custom label styling: `px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-gray-200 peer-checked:bg-blue-500`
- Radio: `class="sr-only peer"`

### Sorting (drag and drop into categories)
Use when: Students classify/categorize/group items. Items go into categories with any number per category.
- Word cards: Class `word-card` (NOT `activity-item`), `data-activity-item`, `data-id`, `draggable="true"`
- Categories: Class `category`, `data-activity-category="category-name"`, must contain `<ul class="word-list"></ul>`
- Color-coded categories: `bg-yellow-200`, `bg-blue-200`, `bg-green-200`, `bg-red-200`, `bg-purple-200`
- Layout: 3-column grid (image, word bank, categories)

### Matching (drag and drop 1-to-1)
Use when: STRICTLY two equal-length lists where each item pairs 1-to-1.
- Draggable items: Class `activity-item`, `data-activity-item="item-N"`, `data-id`, `draggable="true"`
- Drop zones: Class `dropzone`, contain `<div id="dropzone-N" role="region" aria-live="polite"></div>`
- Varied color backgrounds: `bg-yellow-100`, `bg-teal-100`, `bg-pink-100`, etc.

### Fill in the Blank (text inputs)
Use when: Students complete sentences by filling in missing words.
- Input: `<input type="text" data-activity-item="item-N" data-aria-id="aria-X-Y-Z">`
- Inputs inline within text or in structured containers

### Fill in a Table (text inputs in grid)
Use when: Students complete cells in a table or grid.
- Input: `<input type="text" data-activity-item="item-N">` — ALL inputs MUST have `data-activity-item`
- Grid layout: `grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4`

### Open-Ended (textarea)
Use when: Students write free-form answers.
- Input: `<textarea data-aria-id="aria-X-Y-Z" class="w-full p-2 border border-gray-400 rounded min-h-32 resize-none">`
- Warm ambient styling: `bg-amber-50` containers

